{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"secondrate-shelly-coot","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nPopulate `caused_by` deterministically and passively: at bug close, when git blame over the fixed lines yields a clear single culprit commit resolving to a ticket (via the required `rebar-ticket:` trailer), auto-draw the `caused_by` link; expose an optional `--caused-by <ticket|sha>` to augment/override; and add a bug-template advisory telling the debugging agent to blame-hunt and anchor the culprit.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/blame.py` — new: conservative single-culprit blame -> commit -> ticket resolver (reuses the existing `rebar-ticket:` trailer convention).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` — on bug close, best-effort auto-link `caused_by`; honor `--caused-by`.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` — parse `--caused-by`.\n- `docs/user-guide.md` — bug-template advisory (guidance prose; scored, not required).\n- `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_caused_by_autoderive.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nAttributing a bug to a culprit commit is an externally verifiable factual claim (blame is checkable), not an agent self-assessment, so it is safe to derive/accept — unlike process self-report. It reuses git blame + the existing `rebar-ticket:` trailer resolution rather than a novel mechanism. Auto-derivation is conservative: it links only on a single dominant culprit resolving to a ticket; ambiguous cases (refactors, moves, multi-commit) are left to `--caused-by` or `rebar link ... caused_by`. Best-effort — a failed resolution never blocks the close.\n\n## Tests\n- Integration (real temp git repo + store): a bug whose fix edits lines last changed by a single commit carrying a `rebar-ticket:` trailer auto-gets a `caused_by` link to that ticket; an ambiguous multi-commit blame draws no auto-link; `--caused-by <id>` always sets the link.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_caused_by_autoderive.py` passes: closing a bug over a single-culprit fixture yields a `caused_by` link to the resolved ticket (`jq -e '.links[]|select(.relation==\"caused_by\")'`).\n- [ ] an ambiguous two-commit blame yields no auto `caused_by` link — integration test asserts absence.\n- [ ] `rebar transition <bug> in_progress closed --class regression --caused-by <id>` sets the link regardless of blame — test asserts presence.","id":"555e-3efa-4ad6-4169","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Blame-based caused_by auto-derivation + --caused-by param + bug-template advisory"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416825962935001,"uuid":"fd75acb2-5cae-481a-abfa-ce47b3171a69"}